   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>TRUTH LESSONS LEVEL ONE LESSON TWELVE A KEY VIEW OF THE OLD TESTAMENT 6 FROM THE CAPTIVITY TO THE RETURN 1 The prophet during the captivity and in captivity Jeremiah: Rebuking the kings and the people for their sins: Forsaking God and disobeying His word.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>Worshipping idols and committing fornication.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>Speaking lies, deceiving others, and committing iniquity.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>The kings scattering God s people and not caring for them.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>Warning concerning captivity and destruction.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>Weeping for the stiff-necked and unrepentant people.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>The prophets in the land of captivity: Daniel: With his three friends being overcomers in captivity from their youth.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>Praying for the holy city and the holy temple of God until they were recovered.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>Interpreting the image in chapter two and seeing the visions in chapters seven through twelve of his book.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>Ezekiel seeing the visions in the land of captivity concerning the spiritual recovery of God s people: The vision of the wind, the cloud, the fire, and the electrum in chapter one of his book signifying the spiritual revival of God s people.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>God reviving His people and giving them a new heart and a new spirit in chapter thirty-six.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>God s people as the dry bones being revived and formed into God s army in chapter thirty-seven.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>The rebuilding of the holy city and holy temple in chapters forty through forty-eight.</S>
   </TEXT>
